    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-02-27T05:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-02-27T05:24:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861b.6363/112: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-27T12:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1925—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 5:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. <hi rend="italic">Izvestia</hi> 24th. Supreme Soviet People’s Economy applied
                    to Moscow Province Court for the cancellation of the Sakhalin concession
                    contract with the Sinclair Prospecting [<hi rend="italic">Exploration</hi>]
                    Company on the ground that it failed to begin prospecting within the stipulated
                    time and to expend stipulated amounts for technical preparations in connection
                    with such work. Hearing March 11th.<note n="2" xml:id="d562fn2">The Minister in
                        Latvia reported in despatch No. 2762, Apr. 11, 1925, that the Moscow
                        Province Court had annulled the Sinclair contract on March 24. The Minister
                        reported in despatch No. 2947, June 12, 1925, that the Soviet Supreme Court
                        had rejected an appeal by the Sinclair Exploration Co. against the decision
                        of the lower court. (File Nos. 861b.6363/129, 134.)</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
